description: Data was extracted from an older CCLE dataset from Google Genomics on February 2016. Fastqc metric data and deprecated google cloud storage path information are made available here. fields.description: These metrics are derived from the per base sequence quality curve which is a function of the position in the read.  The maximum read-length is divided into 10 equal segments.  The PBSQ10 value is the 10th percentile quality score, and the PBSQ50 value is the median quality score, for bases at that position in the average read.

fields.description: Per Tile Sequence Quality allows you to look at the quality scores from each tile across all of your bases to see if there was a loss in quality associated with only one part of the flowcell. Warning flag is returned if any tile shows a mean Phred score more than 2 less than the mean for that base across all tiles. Fail flag is returned if any tile shows a mean Phred score more than 5 less than the mean for that base across all tiles.
fields.name: PerTileSeqQual

fields.description: Per sequence quality score report allows you to see if a subset of your sequences have universally low quality values. It is often the case that a subset of sequences will have universally poor quality, often because they are poorly imaged (on the edge of the field of view etc), however these should represent only a small percentage of the total sequences.
fields.name: PerSeqQualScore

fields.name: PerBaseSeqCont

fields.description: Describes the average base composition at each position in the average read. The total read-length is divided into 10 equal segments. The PBSC_n_0 fields give the average A/C/T/G percentages seen at the start of each read. The PBSC_n_1 fields give the average A/C/T/G percentages seen 10% into the length of each read, etc, until the PBSC_n_10 fields give the average A/C/T/G percentages seen at the end of each read.

The PBSC_n_1 fields give the average A/C/T/G percentages seen 10% into the length of each read, etc, until the PBSC_n_10 fields give the average A/C/T/G percentages seen at the end of each read.

fields.description: Sequence Length Distribution. High throughput sequencers generate sequence fragments of uniform length, but others can contain reads of wildly varying lengths. Even within uniform length libraries some pipelines will trim sequences to remove poor quality base calls from the end. Warning flag is returned if all sequences are not the same length. Error flag is returned if any of the sequences have zero length.
fields.name: SeqLenDist

fields.description: Duplicate Sequence Level. In a diverse library most sequences will occur only once in the final set. A low level of duplication may indicate a very high level of coverage of the target sequence, but a high level of duplication is more likely to indicate some kind of enrichment bias (eg PCR over amplification). Warning flag is returned if non-unique sequences make up more than 20% of the total. Fail flag is if non-unique sequences make up more than 50% of the total.
fields.name: SeqDupLev
